"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-06-parisolympics-ackelia-smith-second-final-long-jump-progress\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Ackelia Smith qualified for her second final at the Olympics as she advanced in the women's long jump with 6.59m (-0.3m/s) in the prelims on Tuesday morning at Stade de France in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 179, \"end\": 184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999995964891145, \"rank\": 4.0351099927190426e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith, who was seventh in the women's triple jump earlier, was 10th overall.\", \"from\": 187, \"to\": 263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, her compatriot Chanice Porter finished 17th overall and failed to make progress to the top 12.\", \"from\": 264, \"to\": 367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 288, \"end\": 302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chanice_Porter\", \"score\": 0.9999999997393161, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chanice Porter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chanice_Porter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chanice_Porter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith, the Jamaican national champion who qualified for the Olympics by ranking after missing the automatic qualifying mark by one centimetre, was consistent throughout her series on Tuesday, starting with 6.51m (1.2m/s), then registering her best mark in the second round and ending with 6.58m (1.9m/s).\", \"from\": 369, \"to\": 673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 380, \"end\": 388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5469707144598909, \"rank\": 0.7427080007992938, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica_national_footbal